The paper deals with the co-sparse analysis model for signals, which is a topic related to signal processing and compressed sensing. Therefore, cs.SP (Signal Processing), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses theoretical analysis and experiments, which suggest that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be relevant sub-categories.
